  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to use Status on a tablet so that I can use Status on all of my mobile devices.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*:  Status can be used on a iPad, but instead of running at native resolution the viewport is set to an iPhone 4 and everything is scaled up. Whilst the app is usable, it is a horrible user experience and doesn't take advantage of the devices resolution and screen real estate.\r\n\r\n![img_0041 png 2018-06-05 15-11-48](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/41084672-21724e80-6a35-11e8-958b-080d63ed272a.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nStatus runs at native resolution\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nStatus runs at a lower resolution and is scaled up\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n* Make Status a universal app as outlined in [this post](https://shellmonger.com/2017/08/14/universal-ios-apps-with-react-native/).\r\n* Additionally, select all device orientation modes so it works in landscape mode too\r\n* Thoroughly test all screens at different tablet resolutions to ensure layouts look/work as expected\r\n* Fix any display bugs that arise\r\n* Bonus: Get split screen mode working ([similar issue](https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/16152))\r\n\r\n<img width=\"661\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-06-08 at 1 37 33 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/41156300-9e37a360-6b21-11e8-9806-e92ecc465a3b.png\">\r\n",
